definition.value: A hydroxypiperidine that is deoxynojirimycin in which the amino hydrogen is replaced by a butyl group.
An  EC 2.4.1.* (hexosyltransferase) inhibitor that interferes with the activity of ceramide glucosyltransferase (EC 2.4.1.80).
It is used as a prescription medication to relieve repeated attacks of acute intermittent porphyria related to the menstrual cycle in affected women.
A diterpenyl phosphate that is the O-diphospho derivative of tuberculosinol.
A glucotriose consisting of three molecules of alpha-D-glucopyranose joined in a linear sequence by 1->6 glycosidic linkages.
An EC 1.6.5.* (oxidoreductase acting on NADH or NADPH with a quinone or similar as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of NAD(P)H dehydrogenase (quinone), EC 1.6.5.2.
A racemate comprising equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-warfarin(1-).
A dicarboxylic acid monoamide of succinic acid.
A 7-hydroxyisoflavone that is daidzein  substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3'.
Any steroid based on a cholestane skeleton and its derivatives.
Any steroid based on an  androstane skeleton and its derivatives.
Cholesterol esters and free cholesterol which are contained in or bound to lipoproteins.
A role played by a molecular entity used to study the microscopic environment.
An acid or base which exhibits a colour change on neutralization by the basic or acidic titrant at or near the equivalence point of a titration.
Anything used in a scientific experiment that gives a visual change to indicate the presence of a substance or quality, change in a body, etc.
A substance which is adsorbed or desorbed with concomitant colour change at or near the equivalence point of a titration.
A colour indicator that is colourless on one side of the transition interval.
A colour indicator that possesses a different colour on each side of the transition interval.
A methylpyridine carrying a methyl substituent at position 2.
A glycine molecule carrying a 4-hydroxyphenyl substituent.
Members of the class of cholestanoid that include polyhydroxy derivatives of cholestane.
An EC 1.6.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on NADH or NADPH with oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of NAD(P)H oxidase (H2O2-forming), EC 1.6.3.1.
Compounds of structure RSSR' in which R and R' are inorganic groups.

A drug or agent which antagonizes or impairs any mechanism leading to blood platelet aggregation, whether during the phases of activation and shape change or following the dense-granule release reaction and stimulation of the prostaglandin-thromboxane system.
A quinone imine obtained by formal condensation of one of the keto groups of benzoquinone with the amino group of 4-hydroxyaniline.
The (Z)-stereoisomer of glutaconic acid.
